    <div class="info">
      <p> The American Hairless Terrier is a small dog that weighs roughly 12-16 pounds and lives for an average of 14-16 years. They have a short coat length and are described as alert, curious and energetic. </p>

      <p> <a href="https://www.akc.org/dog-breeds/american-hairless-terrier/"> See more information about the American Hairless Terrier from the American Kennel Club. </a> </p>

